  orientation. The practitioner's gaze is now primarily outward and forward:
  toward the community, toward future students, toward the tradition that
  extends beyond the curriculum. The headmaster should use this month for
  genuine one-on-one conversation about each student's vision of their
  post-curriculum path. What community do they intend to maintain contact with?
  Who might they accompany in the future? What would they need to develop
  further in order to guide well?
]

